      [x] _: y Constant Function
Rank_Infinity -- operates on [x and] y as a whole -- WHY_IS_THIS_IMPORTANT?


The value: Infinity (_), whatever [x and] y happen to be.
The argument y can therefore be any noun. Ditto x, if present.
_: has sister-primitives 0:, 1:, 2:, 3:, ... 9: and _1:, _2:, _3:, ... _9:, returning the corresponding integers.
NOTE: there is no primitive: (__:). Use: (__"_) instead.
